---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Features - Aventura">
  <div class="relative flex min-h-screen w-full flex-col overflow-x-hidden">
    <Header currentPath="/features" />

    <main class="flex-1 flex flex-col items-center w-full">
      <!-- Header -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 md:py-16">
        <h1 class="text-text-cream text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-medium leading-tight tracking-tight">
          Features
        </h1>
      </section>

      <!-- Story Modes -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 pb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">Story modes</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Adventure Mode</span> - Interactive fiction with multiple-choice actions. Second-person perspective with dynamic world tracking.</p>
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Creative Writing Mode</span> - Freeform collaborative writing for novels, short stories, and experimental fiction.</p>
          <p>You can write in first, second, or third-person perspective, and choose between past or present tense.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- AI Integration -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">AI providers</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p>Built-in support for OpenRouter, NanoGPT, and any OpenAI-compatible API endpoint.</p>
          <p>Streaming responses, configurable temperature and token limits (up to 1M), and extended thinking support for models that have it.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Memory System -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">Memory system</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p>Automatic chapter summarization keeps context manageable over long stories. The AI retrieves relevant past events when needed.</p>
          <p>Each chapter tracks metadata like keywords, characters involved, locations, and plot threads.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Lorebook -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">Lorebook</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p>Keep track of characters, locations, items, factions, concepts, and events. The AI references your lore automatically to stay consistent.</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">Characters</span> - relationships, status, portraits, descriptions</li>
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">Locations</span> - visit history, discovery status, connections</li>
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">Items</span> - quantities, equipment status, locations</li>
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">Quests</span> - milestones, revelations, plot points</li>
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">Time tracking</span> - year, day, hour, minute per chapter</li>
          </ul>
          <p>An optional AI lore agent can create and update entries as your story progresses. You can also store hidden information that reveals as the story unfolds.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Other Features -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">Other features</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Story branching</span> - Create alternate timelines from any point. Explore "what-if" scenarios without losing the original path.</p>
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Checkpoints</span> - Named snapshots you can export as JSON and restore anytime.</p>
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Network sync</span> - Sync between devices on the same local network with QR code pairing.</p>
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Image generation</span> - Generate scene images with AI. Supports character portraits.</p>
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Text-to-speech</span> - OpenAI-compatible TTS with configurable voice and speed.</p>
          <p><span class="text-text-cream font-medium">Grammar checking</span> - Local grammar checking via Harper.js, no external API needed.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Templates -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">Genre templates</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p>Start with a pre-configured template or create your own. Templates include system prompts, initial world state, and opening scenes.</p>
          <p class="text-text-cream">Fantasy Adventure, Sci-Fi, Mystery, Horror, Slice of Life, or Custom.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Platforms -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">Platforms</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 ml-2">
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">Windows</span> - .exe, .msi</li>
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">macOS</span> - .dmg (Intel & Apple Silicon)</li>
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">Linux</span> - .deb, .rpm, .AppImage</li>
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">Android</span> - .apk</li>
            <li><span class="text-text-cream">iOS</span> - coming soon</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Import/Export -->
      <section class="w-full max-w-4xl px-5 sm:px-10 py-12 border-t border-border-brown/30 mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-cream mb-6">Import & export</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-muted font-body">
          <p>Export stories as JSON or YAML. Import SillyTavern character cards and custom lorebooks.</p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
